The paper deals with scheduling in wireless ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication in computer networks. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also involves optimization problems and graph theory, which are related to information theory and discrete mathematics, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses physical modifications to manipulate the conflict graph of a network, which is related to distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a mixed scheduling strategy for specific networks, which is related to machine learning and optimization. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category.
